<TITLE> Perez to announce Real Madrid candidacy on Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, May 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Florentino Perez will announce on May 14 that he intends to stand in next month's election for the next Real Madrid president, his office said on Monday. "Florentino Perez will make public his intention to stand in the Real Madrid elections on Thursday," his office said in a statement. The announcement would be made at 0930 GMT at a news conference at the Hotel Ritz in Madrid, it added. Perez, who runs one of Europe's largest construction conglomerates ACS, was Real president for six years between 2000 and 2006. He was the architect of the famous 'Galacticos' policy but resigned in February 2006 as the club headed towards their third straight season without a major trophy. Real are being run by interim president Vicente Boluda until elections on June 14, after Ramon Calderon resigned following a vote-rigging scandal in Janu
